12/05/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev, Turkey's Recep Tayyip Erdogan, Croatia's Ivo Sanader, and Romania's Calin Tariceanu participated in a charity football match with several European counterparts in Vienna on Thursday (11 May), on the eve of the EU-Latin America summit. 
Austrian Chancellor Wolfgang Schussel and EC President Jose Barroso led the two teams. 
The game raised funds for a Vienna-based charity that helps homeless children.
The summit includes government leaders from the 25 EU member states and 33 leaders from Latin America and the Caribbean. 
Twelve topics, including energy, trade, development, immigration and the environment will be discussed. 
(Euronews, NTV, BBC, DW - 11/05/06)
